{"id":"285043345_Inconsistency_indicator_maps_on_groups_for_pairwise_comparisons","abstract":"This study presents an abelian group approach to analyzing inconsistency in pairwise comparisons. A notion of an inconsistency indicator map on a group, taking values in an abelian linearly ordered group, is introduced. For it, metrics and generalized metrics are utilized. Every inconsistency indicator map generates both a metric on a group and an inconsistency indicator of an arbitrary pairwise comparisons matrix over the group.","authors":["Waldemar W. Koczkodaj","Jacek Szybowski","Eliza Wajch"],"meta":["November 2015International Journal of Approximate Reasoning 69","DOI:10.1016/j.ijar.2015.11.007","Project: Pairwise comparisons tools and their applications"],"references":["262219187_On_Saaty's_and_Koczkodaj's_inconsistencies_of_pairwise_comparison_matrices","261968013_Pairwise_opposite_matrix_and_its_cognitive_prioritization_operators_Comparisons_with_pairwise_reciprocal_matrix_and_analytic_prioritization_operators","220245233_On_distance-based_inconsistency_reduction_algorithms_for_pairwise_comparisons","284624404_Zur_Einfuhrung_der_transfiniten_Zahlen","270646249_Fast_Convergence_of_Distance-based_Inconsistency_in_Pairwise_Comparisons","268617553_The_Foundations_of_Mathematics","265522931_A_new_approach_to_generalized_metric_spaces","260422757_A_Law_of_Comparative_Judgment","252772394_A_new_definition_of_consistency_of_pairwise_comparisons","251566685_On_Axiomatization_of_Inconsistency_Indicators_for_Pairwise_Comparisons","243057419_The_Amalgamation_Property_for_G-Metric_Spaces","230277769_Representation_and_uniqueness_of_the_Bradley-Terry-Luce_model_for_pair_comparisons","227677336_A_General_Unified_Framework_for_Pairwise_Comparison_Matrices_in_Multicriterial_Methods","221955622_A_Scaling_Method_for_Priorities_in_Hierarchical_Structures","221678018_A_Law_of_Comparative_Judgment","220647639_Pairwise_classifier_combination_using_belief_functions","220494918_A_Different